<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2994&amp;p=14057#p14057"><![CDATA[
I still don't understand what the problem is. Is it:<br />1) The Update shortcut doesn't show up in the start screen<br />2) The Update shortcut doesn't show up in the start menu<br />3) The Classic Shell folder doesn't show up in the start menu<br /><br />All of these should be happening for Windows 8. For Windows 8.1 #1 may not happen, because the start screen by default shows a small set of pinned programs. But if you click on the down arrow at the bottom you will see all programs, including the Classic Shell Update.<br /><br />Besides, why do you need the Update tool to be easily available? The check for new versions should be happening automatically and the tool will pop up if needed.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Sat Jul 19, 2014 10:51 am</p><hr />
