<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2994&amp;p=14052#p14052"><![CDATA[
Actually I had to go to search option in Windows 8 and I found the Classic Shell Folder and the Icon is in there, but NOT the app.  So I created a shortcut for the Classic Shell Update.<br /> <br />The &quot;All Programs&quot; feature shows up in Windows 7, NOT in Windows 8 or 8.1.  Also, Classic Shell's folder DOES NOT show up in &quot;Programs&quot; section of Windows Start Menu either for Windows 8/8.1.  You have to create a shortcut for it once you find it in the Search option under File Explorer or Windows Explorer on your computer.  So that is what I did just now, and that works fine as a workaround.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4175">LeiaSolo</a> — Sat Jul 19, 2014 5:01 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
